We plan with Jira data we've never validated.

PlanReady is a Jira data health assessment tool designed for Optus teams. It tells us whether our data is trustworthy enough for planning, forecasting, and decision-making — before we rely on it.

14
Health Dimensions
7
Business Outcomes
4
Trust Lenses

Every planning decision at Optus depends on Jira data nobody has validated.

?

Complete?

Is all work actually captured in Jira, or are significant efforts invisible to our planning tools and leadership reporting?

?

Fresh?

Does Jira reflect the current state of work across our teams, or are statuses days behind reality?

?

Consistent?

Are estimates and issue types used the same way across Optus teams, or does every squad have its own dialect?

?

Trustworthy?

Can we defend the accuracy of our velocity, burndowns, and capacity forecasts when leadership asks?

"The data is in Jira" is not the same as "the data is reliable." The cost of this assumption compounds with every sprint, every roadmap, every commitment we make.

A systematic, multi-dimensional health assessment for our Jira data.

PlanReady analyses Jira data across four trust lenses, fourteen health dimensions organised into five clusters, mapping findings to seven business outcomes that matter to Optus.

How It Works

1

Configure

Select your Optus team, set a date range, choose which issue types and dimensions to assess, and configure field mappings — all through a guided wizard.

2

Assess

PlanReady analyses your team's Jira data across all selected dimensions, comparing results against peer teams within Optus and historical trends.

3

Improve

Get a Composite Health Score, outcome confidence ratings, and prioritised improvement plays with effort/impact guidance tailored to your team.

One score. Complete transparency.

The Composite Health Score (CHS) combines current state, trajectory, and peer comparison into a single, defensible number for every Optus team.

See where your team stands across Optus.

PlanReady doesn't assess teams in isolation. Every score is contextualised against a configurable comparison group of peer teams within the organisation.

  • Percentile ranking across all 14 dimensions
  • Trajectory comparison — is your team improving faster or slower than peers?
  • Confidence intervals on every score, so you know how precise the measurement is
  • Compare by methodology, team size, volume, tribe, or hand-pick specific Optus teams

Know what's wrong. Know what to do about it.

PlanReady doesn't just diagnose — it prescribes. Every assessment includes a prioritised improvement plan tailored to the team's specific gaps.

  • Pre-built improvement plays mapped to each dimension
  • Effort vs. impact prioritisation to find quick wins
  • Task-level guidance with clear acceptance criteria
  • Impact tracking to measure whether changes actually moved the needle

Three personas. One platform.

PlanReady is designed for every stakeholder in the Jira data health lifecycle at Optus.

🎯

Creator

Configures assessments through the guided wizard, selecting teams, dimensions, and comparison groups. Runs assessments and reviews results.

📈

Viewer

Consumes assessment results, tracks health scores over time, and monitors improvement progress. Read-only access to team dashboards.

⚙️

Admin

Manages organisation-wide settings, team attributes, default configurations, and user permissions. Sets governance guardrails across Optus.

Role-based access control
Organisation-wide defaults
Team attribute auto-assignment
Audit trail for all assessments

Rigorous scoring you can defend.

The Composite Health Score is transparent, reproducible, and grounded in statistical methodology — not arbitrary thresholds.

CHS = CSS(50%) + TRS(35%) + PGS(15%)

Current State + Trajectory + Peer Growth

Category Score Range Description
Excellent 70 – 100 Significantly above baseline with strong trajectory
Good 55 – 69 Above baseline with positive direction
Average 45 – 54 Near baseline, stable performance
Below Average 30 – 44 Under baseline, needs attention
Needs Attention 0 – 29 Significantly below baseline, intervention required
🔍

Coverage

Is all work captured? Are fields filled? Do estimates exist? Measures the completeness of Jira data.

🛡️

Integrity

Is the data internally consistent? Are there antipatterns, hollow fields, or conflicting information?

⏱️

Timing

Is data fresh? Are updates happening in real-time or in retrospective bulk batches?

👥

Behavioural

Are teams actively collaborating in Jira? Are processes being followed consistently?
